{"parse":{"title":"Academia pro Interlingua","pageid":1080881,"revid":791778436,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\nThe <b>Academia pro Interlingua</b> was an organization dedicated to the promotion of <a href=\"/wiki/International_auxiliary_language\" title=\"International auxiliary language\">international auxiliary languages</a>, and is associated in particular with Prof. <a href=\"/wiki/Giuseppe_Peano\" title=\"Giuseppe Peano\">Giuseppe Peano</a>'s language <a href=\"/wiki/Latino_sine_flexione\" title=\"Latino sine flexione\">Latino sine flexione</a> (Latin without inflections).\n</p><p>The <i>Academia</i> was a descendant of the <i>Kadem bev\u00fcnetik volap\u00fcka</i> (<a href=\"/wiki/International_Academy_of_Volap%C3%BCk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"International Academy of Volap\u00fck\">International Academy of Volap\u00fck</a>) created at a <a href=\"/wiki/Volap%C3%BCk\" title=\"Volap\u00fck\">Volap\u00fck</a> congress in <a href=\"/wiki/Munich\" title=\"Munich\">Munich</a> in August 1887. Under <a href=\"/wiki/Waldemar_Rosenberger\" title=\"Waldemar Rosenberger\">Waldemar Rosenberger</a>, who became the director in 1892, this group had transformed Volap\u00fck into <a href=\"/wiki/Idiom_Neutral\" title=\"Idiom Neutral\">Idiom Neutral</a> and changed its name to <i>Akademi Internasional de Lingu Universal</i> in 1898.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg/220px-Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"310\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg/330px-Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg/440px-Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1317\" data-file-height=\"1857\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Page_N._1_of_Academia_pro_Interlingua%27s_journal_Discussiones.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>N. 1 of Academia pro Interlingua's journal <i>Discussiones</i> (1909)</div></div></div>\n<p>When the <i>Akademi</i> effectively chose to abandon Idiom Neutral in favor of Latino sine flexione in 1908, it elected Peano as its director, and the name of the group was changed to <i>Academia pro Interlingua</i> since <i>Interlingua</i> was an alternative name for Peano's language. The original <i>Academia pro Interlingua</i> survived until about 1939.\n</p><p>The official journals of the \"Academia\" were \"Discussiones\" (1909\u201313), \"Circulares\" (1915\u201324), and \"Academia pro Interlingua\" (1925\u201327). They have been recently published in a CD-Rom by the mathematics department of the university of <a href=\"/wiki/Turin\" title=\"Turin\">Turin</a>.\n<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> They show a collective attempt to propagate, in a democratic way, an international language to facilitate the scientific reports among nations, favouring the progress of civilization and culture.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Concerning_Interlingua_de_IALA_.28IA.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Concerning_Interlingua_de_IALA_(IA)\">Concerning <a href=\"/wiki/Interlingua_de_IALA\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Interlingua de IALA\">Interlingua de IALA</a> (IA)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Academia_pro_Interlingua&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Concerning Interlingua de IALA (IA)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Today the name <b><a href=\"/wiki/Interlingua\" title=\"Interlingua\">Interlingua</a></b> often refers to a different language presented in 1951 by the <a href=\"/wiki/International_Auxiliary_Language_Association\" title=\"International Auxiliary Language Association\">International Auxiliary Language Association</a> (IALA). Advocates for IA currently use, among others, the name <i>Academia pro Interlingua</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Academia_pro_Interlingua&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Silvia Roero, Clara (coord.) (2003). <i>Le Riviste di Giuseppe Peano</i> <cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110722063830/http://www.dm.unito.it/collanacdrom/index.html\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dm.unito.it/collanacdrom/index.html\">the original</a> on 22 July 2011<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2011-03-01</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dm.unito.it%2Fcollanacdrom%2Findex.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAcademia+pro+Interlingua\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> (CD-Rom N. 4). Mathematics Department of University of Turin.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://interlingua.wikia.com\">Academia pro Interlingua</a> (IA), wiki in IALA's Interlingua for a current organization using the name</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Academia_pro_Interlingua&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>web.archive.org/web/<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/academiaprointerlingua190913/home\">https://sites.google.com/site/academiaprointerlingua190913/home</a>, site on <i>Discussiones</i>, the first journal of Academia pro Interlingua (1909\u201313).</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1329\nCached time: 20180907183526\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.060 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.082 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 157/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1805/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 99/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1581/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.021/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.45 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   63.557      1 -total\n 50.91%   32.357      1 Template:Cite_web\n 45.46%   28.895      1 Template:Use_dmy_dates\n 17.85%   11.346      1 Template:DMCA\n 15.18%    9.645      1 Template:Dated_mainten